[I] A system profiler and benchmark for Linux systems

[T] HardInfo is a system profiler and benchmark for Linux systems.
[T] It is able to obtain information from both hardware and basic software,
[T] and organize them in a simple to use GUI.

[U] https://hardinfo2.org/

[A] Leandro A. F. Pereira
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

[C] extra/tool
[F] OBJDIR CROSS

[L] GPL
[V] 2.3.1

[D] d10bff8d77f48f60040b735850f1ecf22dffe0a396c7208e699f26b8 hardinfo2-2.3.1.tar.gz https://github.com/hardinfo2/hardinfo2/archive/refs/tags/release-2.3.1/

var_append GCC_WRAPPER_APPEND ' ' -I$root$(pkgprefix includedir libxcb)
var_remove_regex CC_WRAPPER_INSERT ' ' "-O[0-9sz]"
pkginstalled qt5base || var_append cmakeopt ' ' -DHARDINFO2_QT5=OFF
pkginstalled libsoup3 || var_append cmakeopt ' ' -DHARDINFO2_LIBSOUP3=OFF
